verbose_text: Activation of the calyx of Held input via electric fiber stimulation at the midline showed an increase in alpha-amino-3-hydroxy-5-methyl-4-isoxazolepropionic acid receptor (AMPAR) conductance from 132.7 +/- 16.0 nS (n = 18) in WT to 187.9 +/- 14.5 nS (n = 17; P = 0.015) in dfw 2J / dfw 2J, while decay time constants were unchanged between genotypes (XREF_FIG).
